        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:11PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Eads, or 27 miles north of Lamar, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eads, Chivington, and Brandon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
